////Files Used:
1. PerformSelection.cc, BuildFile - place in CMSSW_3_3_0/src/Analysis/SimpleExamples/bin :
These are used to create the PerformSelection.exe (via scram b), which in turn runs over the PAT tuples and generates 
  a) the output .root file with the Event Tree. 
  b) the .txt table, which contains the information on how many events pass the cuts. E.g. 
    PerformSelection.exe inputFiles=/uscms_data/d2/ilyao/MadGraph/TTbarMG_sample107.root \outputEvery=1000 /uscms_data/d2/ilyao/MadGraph/First100KEvts/TTbarMG_outfile.root First100K_TTbarMG_Params.txt
    
    -Note that there is a hack in place, which requires that the user defined output files above, be the last two listed on the command line.
    -The .txt table is then used by MakeSelectionTable.C

2. MakeSelectionTable.C - place in CMSSW_3_3_0/src/ :
A macro, which reads in the input tables for the desired processes and produces the final SelectionTable.

3. InputXSections_PerformSelectionMG.txt - 
A listing of input CrossSections & Filter efficiencies for the madgraph MC.
  
4. CRAB_Launch_Files: QCDPY.py  QCD_HT100to250MG.py  STopSMG.py  STopTMG.py  TTbarMG.py  TTbarPY.py  TTbarPY.py~  VVpJMG.py  WWPY.py  WZPY.py  WpJMG.py  ZZPY.py  ZpJMG.py - place in CMSSW_3_3_5/src/ :
Generate the corresponding PAT tuples via CRAB.
MG=MadGraph
PY=PYTHIA
The Monte Carlo is obtained from https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/viewauth/CMS/ProductionSummer2009at7TeV .

